lines_and_colors: It can't be summer,  that got through;
There 's that long town of white to cross
It can't be dying,  it's too rouge,
The dead shall go in white.
So sunset shuts my question down
document.title: It can't be summer,  that got through;
document.publication: Poems by Emily Dickinson: Second Series, Higginson and Todd, 1891
